# nyc-marathon.ledger — extracted from a ChatGPT-generated NYC Marathon plan
# (July 20 – Nov 1, 2026) provided by the athlete's sister on 2026-07-19.
# Consent recorded: use in repo approved, anonymous ("my sister"), no name.
# race_priority: goal — declared by the plan itself ("Goal: Approximately
# 5:00 marathon"; the entire plan builds to Nov 1) and confirmed by the athlete.
# All run sessions are stated in MILES with pace RANGES (e.g. "12:30–13:30+
# per mile"), so no single duration is computable without the athlete stating
# times — durations are "-" per ledger rules; stated rest days are 0.
# Excluded as unquantifiable/undatable (reported in editor findings, not rows):
#  - Weeks 4–5 (Aug 10–23, travel): runs listed without weekdays or dates
#  - Week 6 "Tue/Wed 3–4 easy" (ambiguous day) — Thu/Sat/Sun of week 6 kept
#  - Recurring bike (45–75 min ranges), swim, strength (20–30 min ranges)
# ATHLETE STATEMENT recorded 2026-07-19 (from the plan's runner, the
# athlete's sister): "easy pace is about a 12 minute mile." Run durations
# below are miles x 12 min/mile per that statement. Conversion rules, noted
# for direction-safety:
#  - preceding-period ranges use the LOWER mile count (understates preceding
#    load; can only make the gate HARDER to pass — safe)
#  - race-week ranges use the UPPER mile count (overstates race week — safe)
#  - her stated 12:00/mi is faster than the plan's prescribed easy range
#    (12:30-13:30/mi), so all run durations may be slight understatements;
#    for race week this is noted and immaterial: the margin below is ~6x
#  - Wed race-week "optional easy swim/rest": SECOND ATHLETE STATEMENT
#    recorded 2026-07-19 — "she'd take the rest." Recorded as 0 min per her
#    declaration; the rest option is the plan's own, chosen by the athlete.
plan_start: 2026-07-20
race_date: 2026-11-01
race_priority: goal

